== Japanese ==
[[Image:Japanese Katakana A.png|thumb|right|Katakana character ア]]
===Etymology===
Simplified in the [[w:Heian period|Heian period]] from the ''[[man'yōgana]]'' ([[万葉仮名]]) kanji [[阿]] (''a''), taken from the left part of the character.

===Katakana character===
'''ア''' (''a'')

# the [a] phoneme, typically in words of non-Japanese origins
#: The first character of the [[katakana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to [[あ]] (''a'') in the [[hiragana]] syllabary. The next katakana character is [[イ]] (''i'').

